ed</gtr:status><gtr:grantCategory>Fellowship</gtr:grantCategory><gtr:grantReference>ES/H043845/1</gtr:grantReference><gtr:abstractText>&lt;p>The project, which will be undertaken by Dr. Gianluca Parolin, an Associate Professor in the Department of Law, American University in Cairo, Egypt. It&amp;nbsp;examines interfaith marriages (IFMs) in an interdisciplinary context, using Islamic legal studies, comparative law and reflections drawn from contemporary theories of citizenship as the initial tools of reflection for building a conceptual model, which will then be tested out in the specific context of Scotland and the Scottish legal system. &lt;/p>

&lt;p>The project builds upon Parolin's previous doctoral work on citizenship regulations in the Arab world (published as a monography by Amsterdam University Press in 2009) and more recent work on citizenship regulations in Lebanon and Egypt, undertaken at the behest of the EUDO-Citizenship observatory (&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.eudo-citizenship.eu/&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;>www.eudo-citizenship.eu&lt;/a>) of which Shaw, the Edinburgh applicant, is a co-director.&lt;br />&lt;/p></gtr:abstractText><gtr:fund><gtr:end>2010-10-31</gtr:end><gtr:funder url="http://gtr.ukri.org:80/organisation/924BE15C-91F2-4AAD-941A-3F338324B6AE"><gtr:id>924BE15C-91F2-4AAD-941A-3F338324B6AE</gtr:id><gtr:name>ESRC</gtr:name></gtr:funder><gtr:start>2010-05-01</gtr:start><gtr:type>INCOME_ACTUAL</gtr:type><gtr:valuePounds>5160</gtr:valuePounds></gtr:fund><gtr:output><gtr:artisticAndCreativeProductOutputs/><gtr:collaborationOutputs/><gtr:disseminationOutputs/><gtr:exploitationOutputs/><gtr:furtherFundingOutputs/><gtr:impactSummaryOutputs/><gtr:intellectualPropertyOutputs/><gtr:otherResearchOutputs/><gtr:policyInfluenceOutputs/><gtr:productOutputs/><gtr:researchDatabaseAndModelOutputs/><gtr:researchMaterialOutputs/><gtr:softwareAndTechnicalProductOutputs/><gtr:spinOutOutputs/></gtr:output><gtr:publications><gtr:publication><gtr:id>EC2BBE16-2EA7-43E3-88B0-1D7F9C3BE672</gtr:id><gtr:title>Interfaith marriages and Muslim communities in Scotland</gtr:title><gtr:authors><gtr:author url="http://gtr.ukri.org:80/person/80c4ba2a145db993e1ae5e0aebce285c"><gtr:id>80c4ba2a145db993e1ae5e0aebce285c</gtr:id><gtr:otherNames>Gianluca Parolin (Author)</gtr:otherNames></gtr:author></gtr:authors><gtr:date>2011-01-01</gtr:date><gtr:outcomeId>r_5016506084cb65f208</gtr:outcomeId></gtr:publication><gtr:publication><gtr:id>14BC5ECF-FB00-4BB7-98B5-E16418DE4005</gtr:id><gtr:title>Invisible Barriers to Citizenship? Islamic Inter-Faith Marriages in Europe</gtr:title><gtr:authors><gtr:author url="http://gtr.ukri.org: